# PostgreSQL Initialization Scripts
# 
# These SQL scripts run automatically on first container start
# Execution order: alphabetical (01, 02, 03, ...)
#
# Current scripts:
# 01-create-databases.sql          - Creates application databases
# 02-create-extensions.sql         - Installs PostgreSQL extensions (UUID, pgcrypto, pg_trgm)
# 03-create-tables.sql             - Creates all application tables
# 04-create-indexes.sql            - Adds performance indexes
# 05-create-functions-triggers.sql - Database functions and triggers
# 06-insert-sample-data.sql        - Inserts sample data and creates views
# 07-create-users-permissions.sql  - Creates application users with appropriate permissions
#
# To add custom scripts:
# - Name them with numeric prefix (e.g., 08-my-script.sql)
# - Use \c database_name to switch databases
# - Scripts run as postgres superuser
#
# Default credentials created:
# - admin user: admin / admin123 (⚠️ CHANGE THIS!)
# - app_user: app_password (⚠️ CHANGE THIS!)
# - readonly_user: readonly_password (⚠️ CHANGE THIS!)
